The body of a one-year old baby that fell into a borehole pit at Joppie village in Nâ€™wamitwa outside Tzaneen in Limpopo has been retrieved. It took the emergency services personnel about two days to retrieve and bring the body to surface. The Mopani District Municipality has launched an investigation to establish circumstances around the borehole that was allegedly left uncovered in the yard of a local headman. The district's Executive Mayor Nkakareng Rakgoale who was accompanied by the Greater Tzaneen Municipality's Mayor Maripe Mangena has applauded the disaster management rescue team, the police and construction workers who were brought on board to assist the situation. The scene has been handed over to the SAPS for further investigations. Rakgoale has sent her message of condolences to the family of the deceased.